one call. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\';\">All our levels of service include some amount of this kind of help. We&rsquo;re like that tech-savvy friend that so many people have. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\';\">Come to think of it, we&rsquo;re also a friend of that friend. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\'; font-weight: bold;\">We&rsquo;re the Expert&rsquo;s Expert when you need one </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\';\">Here&rsquo;s where things get interesting (or complicated, if you&rsquo;re not a computer person at heart). Could be you have a flat ethernet network with 524 end-users and a few server farms. The network performance is poor from time to time and you&rsquo;re not sure what to do next. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\';\">You&rsquo;ve asked your in-house IT to do analysis and possibly redesign the current infrastructure to improve performance. Your employee is top-notch and usually takes any problem and<br /> just handles it. This time, however, the initial response to your request was an expression of excitement that slowly degenerated into abject terror. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\';\">Your IT experts have not kept up with technology. They&rsquo;re not sure what to do next, either. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\';\">Of course this scenario is quite a bit better than having an under-qualified, over-confident staff member just diving in and hoping they can swim. It takes training, experience, and life-long learning to avoid drowning in an ocean of routers, cables, switches, and CPUs. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.000000pt; font-family: \'Arial\';\">This is another reason we&rsquo;re here &ndash; to be your IT expe